	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p><addressee>Rev. Mr. Isaac Leeser</addressee> <placeName>Pha</placeName></p>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Norfolk</placeName> <date>April 22&#47;66</date></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Esteemed Sir and Brother&#33;</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><sic>Thankfull</sic> &#38;<lb/> obliged to you for the large amount of<lb/> attention paid unto me since late&#44;<lb/> I beg to inform you&#44; that on<lb/> request of the <placeName>Norfolk</placeName> Institute<lb/> I paid them a visit &#38; gave them<lb/> a lecture yesterday at their divine<lb/> service &#40;<add>hebrew</add>&#41;. As I hear acer&#45;<lb/>tain <persName>Mr. or Dr Bean</persName> residing in <placeName>N. York</placeName><lb/> &#38; recommended by <persName>Messrs Rev. <hi rend="underline">Einhorn</hi></persName><lb/> &#38; <hi rend="underline"><persName>Adler</persName></hi>&#44; <placeName>N.Y.</placeName>&#44; is the other party&#44;<lb/> I am to <sic>compede</sic> with. Do you&#44;<lb/> esteemed Sir&#44; know the party&#44; is he<lb/> &#40;<persName>Mr. Bean</persName>&#41; not one of the <hi rend="underline">very radical</hi> party&#63;<lb/> If so&#44; you would oblige me to the highest<lb/> degree by communicating such to the <placeName>Norfolk</placeName></p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>Institute Board&#44; but <hi rend="underline">without mentioning</hi>&#44;<lb/> <hi rend="underline">anything of this letter</hi>&#44; being now certain<lb/> that your <hi rend="underline">word</hi> has some great in&#45;<lb/>fluence on the Norfolkers &#38; would make<lb/> a <hi rend="underline">big stroke</hi> through <hi rend="underline"><persName>Mr Beans</persName> </hi>account.<lb/> So far as I see&#44; I have a very good<lb/> chance&#44; but <hi rend="underline"><persName>Bean</persName></hi> has some patronizers<lb/> too&#44; it would therefore be of great<lb/> advantage for my part&#44; if you<lb/> would oblige me by complying with<lb/> the above. As the cause will be<lb/> decided on <date>Saturday</date> next&#44; your<lb/> letter would have to arrive here before<lb/> that time. Excuse&#44; Sir&#44; the lot of<lb/> trouble I have put unto you &#38; be<lb/> honored&#44; that gratitude on my<lb/> part will always be my first<lb/> aim.  Yours most obdt. servant</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)"><persName role="author">E L Hess</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(4)"><placeName>19 W. Balto St</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(5)"><placeName>Balto</placeName></p>
				<p>P.S. <sic>Adress</sic> the letter</p>
				<p><persName>J Hofheimer</persName></p>
				<p>President of the <placeName>Norfolk</placeName> English &#38; Hebrew Institute</p>
			<p rend="indent(6)"><placeName>Norfolk Va</placeName></p>
				<p>I will leave here tomorrow for <placeName>Balto</placeName>.</p>
			
